by NileCat » Wed 09.30.2009 7:01 am Thank you very much, tokai-san.I'm sorry. I carefully fabricated the question. When I was at school, I learned like this: The only correct answer was:** Anyway, my teacher said in the last class,"two cups of coffee, please". **Because grammar required me to do so. And my teachers never told me the truth.Besides, the word "grammar" itself irritates me every now and then.http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/GrammarIf you look for the word "grammars"(plural) in that page, you could find 10 cases...Oh, my goodness!I suppose many of you who are learning Japanese would share my feelings of desperation.Thanks, anyways ! NileCat
