Re: A strange question about English
by kurisuto » Wed 09.30.2009 10:58 am NileCat wrote:Uが単数（Uncountable)でPが複数（Plural)です。Just a little point : don't confuse "singular" and "uncountable", they're not the same. "Grammar" (as in "English grammar", i.e a set of rules or even a book about this set of rules) is singular and countable, or rather, it is a countable word whose singular form is "grammar", and it can be pluralized ; but in another acception, "grammar" refers to a field of study not necessarily related to a single language, in which case it's singular and uncountable.
kurisuto
